definitions: The capital city of New Zealand, located at the southwestern tip of the North Island.
A type of boot made of rubber or waterproof material, also known as a 'Wellington boot'.
A dish consisting of beef coated with pâté and duxelles, wrapped in puff pastry and baked.
examples: Wellington is known for its vibrant arts scene.
She wore her Wellingtons in the rain.
They served beef Wellington at the dinner party.
